**3. Write a short story of the three little pigs who met the little red riding hood.**

The three little pigs, Pip, Pop, and Percy, were enjoying a lovely afternoon in their sturdy brick house. Pip was tending the vegetable garden, Pop was practicing his flute, and Percy was meticulously polishing the chimney. Suddenly, a knock echoed through the house.

"Who's there?" called Pip cautiously.

"It's Little Red Riding Hood!" a sweet voice replied. "I'm taking a basket of goodies to my grandmother, but I've lost my way in the woods and I'm terribly frightened."

Percy, ever the practical one, peered out the window. "She looks quite distressed! Let her in, Pip."

Little Red Riding Hood, clutching her basket, stepped inside. She was indeed a little shaken. "Thank you so much," she said, her voice trembling. "I heard there was a big, bad wolf lurking about."

Pop stopped playing his flute. "A wolf, you say? We know all about wolves! We built this house to withstand even the strongest huffs and puffs." He puffed out his chest proudly.

Little Red Riding Hood’s eyes widened. "Really? That's wonderful! My grandmother lives deep in the woods, and I'm worried about getting there safely."

Pip, always the kindest, offered, "We'll escort you! Percy, you take the lead, Pop, keep an eye out for trouble, and I'll carry Little Red's basket for a while."

And so, the three little pigs and Little Red Riding Hood set off through the woods. Percy, with his keen sense of direction, led the way. Pop’s flute music kept their spirits high, and Pip’s cheerful chatter eased Little Red’s fears. They encountered no wolf, only friendly squirrels and singing birds.

Finally, they reached Little Red Riding Hood’s grandmother’s cottage.  The grandmother, delighted to see her granddaughter safe and sound, thanked the pigs profusely.

"You're all very brave and kind," she said. "Come in and share some of my berry pie!"

And so, the three little pigs and Little Red Riding Hood enjoyed a delicious pie together, proving that even the most different creatures can become the best of friends when they help each other.



